ocial security number).'=>'When renting a product for the first time, it will have to be validated as lessee to rent on our platform. As part of this, we must verify your identity and whether you meet the requirements to rent on our platform. We can ask you to verify your identity through an external service authorized as NemID, as well as upload a photo of your face, photos of your drivers license, national identity document,national health insurance card and/or passport. The images they will be deleted after one year. Your identification number personal, provided through uploaded photos, may be used to deal with customers, insurance or criminal proceedings arising on a rental reservation. Also, as a security measure additionally, we may perform a credit check and/or ask you to provide additional documentation, such as a proof of address or a copy of a pay stub recent. For payroll, we check if the user is employee with an additional input to the information of the address. The documentation of your validation to rent will be store while you are validated to rent on the platform and it is eliminated a year later. If your validation as a tenant not approved, your photos are deleted one year after submitting your request. Documentation is kept if necessary in connection with a criminal or insurance investigation stemming from a rent. Additional documentation of the approval of the lessee is stored for one year after his presentation. It is retained in case it is necessary in connection with a criminal or insurance investigation stemming from a rent. By renting a product as a lessee, the owner can ask for a photo of his driving license taken through the GoMore app to verify that the person picking up the vehicle is the same as the authorized person for rent by GoMore. The information processing of aforementioned identity authentication is based on your consent (article 6 (1) (a) of the GDPR) (information not confidential) and paragraph 2 of article 11 of the Danish Law on data protection (social security number).',
