    'The data controller is the one who decides the purpose for which your personal data is used, in this case, Olatz Rivera Olmedo. with DNI 79068106V and registered office at [Calle Batalla de Arapiles 4, Escalera Derecha, 2D 50004 Zaragoza] You can contact our privacy manager at the following email:'=>'The data controller is the one who decides the purpose for which your personal data is used, in this case, Olatz Rivera Olmedo. with DNI 79068106V and registered office at [Calle Batalla de Arapiles 4, Escalera Derecha, 2D 50004 Zaragoza] You can contact our privacy manager at the following email:',
    'Your personal data will be processed for: a. Manage queries or requests received, based on your consent. b. Provide our customer service (solve incidents and doubts you have had when using KnockKnock products, such as shared trips, rentals between individuals or renting), either at your request or because of our need for service management. The basis of legitimacy in these cases will be your consent or the contractual relationship you have with us. c. Make recommendations on improvements and optimization of the use of our services, such as improvements that you can make in the user profile to increase your rental requests, offer you the installation of keyless devices, renew your rental contract or offer you the possibility of improving the contracted products, based on your consent. d. Send you promotions and offers about our services, based on your consent.'=>'Your personal data will be processed for: a. Manage queries or requests received, based on your consent. b. Provide our customer service (solve incidents and doubts you have had when using KnockKnock products, such as shared trips, rentals between individuals or renting), either at your request or because of our need for service management. The basis of legitimacy in these cases will be your consent or the contractual relationship you have with us. c. Make recommendations on improvements and optimization of the use of our services, such as improvements that you can make in the user profile to increase your rental requests, offer you the installation of keyless devices, renew your rental contract or offer you the possibility of improving the contracted products, based on your consent. d. Send you promotions and offers about our services, based on your consent.',
    'Before storing your password, we apply a cryptographically secure hashing algorithm to it. This means that even if data is stolen from our servers, your password is safe.'=>'Before storing your password, we apply a cryptographically secure hashing algorithm to it. This means that even if data is stolen from our servers, your password is safe.',
    'Portions of your public profile page, such as your first name and last initial, personal description, education, occupation, age, and average platform response time are publicly visible to other users. If you rent your product or offer a ride on our platform, information related to your trip or product will be publicly available. The transportation or rental list pages will also display some information about you, including your name, car registration number, average response time and acceptance fee (rental only), and age. If you delete information you have posted to KnockKnock, copies may remain viewable in cached and archived pages, or if other users have copied or saved that information. After completing a reservation, users can write comments and rate each other. Reviews are part of your public profile page.'=>'Portions of your public profile page, such as your first name and last initial, personal description, education, occupation, age, and average platform response time are publicly visible to other users. If you rent your product or offer a ride on our platform, information related to your trip or product will be publicly available. The transportation or rental list pages will also display some information about you, including your name, car registration number, average response time and acceptance fee (rental only), and age. If you delete information you have posted to KnockKnock, copies may remain viewable in cached and archived pages, or if other users have copied or saved that information. After completing a reservation, users can write comments and rate each other. Reviews are part of your public profile page.',
    'We only use industry standard encryption algorithms and well tested code libraries. Our database, as well as all of our application servers, are powered by Amazon Web Services (AWS), and we rely on Amazons infrastructure and physical security measures.'=>'We only use industry standard encryption algorithms and well tested code libraries. Our database, as well as all of our application servers, are powered by Amazon Web Services (AWS), and we rely on Amazons infrastructure and physical security measures.',
    'When ordering a rental car through KnockKnock, you are asked to provide name and email (if you are not a registered user), address, telephone number, date of birth, driving record for the last three years, and number social security or national identity card. This is necessary to complete the order with our leasing partners. Social Security or National ID number is required to perform a credit check. It is deleted one week after you have placed your online order. KnockKnock obtains your consent to carry out a credit check (article 6 (1) (a) of the GDPR). The other personal data obtained for the purpose of leasing a vehicle is necessary for the performance of the rental agreement (Article 6, paragraph 1, letter b) of the GDPR) and necessary for the fulfillment of legal obligations (Article 1, paragraph 1, letter c). ), of GDPR).'=>'When ordering a rental car through KnockKnock, you are asked to provide name and email (if you are not a registered user), address, telephone number, date of birth, driving record for the last three years, and number social security or national identity card. This is necessary to complete the order with our leasing partners. Social Security or National ID number is required to perform a credit check. It is deleted one week after you have placed your online order. KnockKnock obtains your consent to carry out a credit check (article 6 (1) (a) of the GDPR). The other personal data obtained for the purpose of leasing a vehicle is necessary for the performance of the rental agreement (Article 6, paragraph 1, letter b) of the GDPR) and necessary for the fulfillment of legal obligations (Article 1, paragraph 1, letter c). ), of GDPR).',
    'We reserve the right to modify this Privacy Policy or related procedures at any time in accordance with this provision. We will post the updated Privacy Policy on the KnockKnock Platform and update the "Last Updated" date at the top of this page. Changes to KnockKnocks privacy policy are effective when posted on this page. Your continued use of the KnockKnock services after these changes means that you accept the revised Privacy Policy. If you do not agree to these changes, you may choose to close your account with us.'=>'We reserve the right to modify this Privacy Policy or related procedures at any time in accordance with this provision. We will post the updated Privacy Policy on the KnockKnock Platform and update the "Last Updated" date at the top of this page. Changes to KnockKnocks privacy policy are effective when posted on this page. Your continued use of the KnockKnock services after these changes means that you accept the revised Privacy Policy. If you do not agree to these changes, you may choose to close your account with us.',
    'When you sign up, you will need to provide your full name, an email, and a password. The processing of the account information is necessary for the performance of the contract with you (article 6 (1) (b) of the GDPR).'=>'When you sign up, you will need to provide your full name, an email, and a password. The processing of the account information is necessary for the performance of the contract with you (article 6 (1) (b) of the GDPR).',
    'When registering a car that can be used for rental, you must provide information about the car, including the make and model, car registration number, car address, and insurance status. You can also provide additional images and descriptions of the products features so that you can market it to other users. When registering a rideshare product, you can provide information about the make and model, the products license plate number, the number of seats, and photos of the product. The processing of vehicle information is necessary for the performance of the contract with you (Article 6 (1) (b) of the GDPR) and KnockKnocks legitimate interest in providing the best possible services on the platform (article 6 (1) (f) of GDPR).'=>'When registering a car that can be used for rental, you must provide information about the car, including the make and model, car registration number, car address, and insurance status. You can also provide additional images and descriptions of the products features so that you can market it to other users. When registering a rideshare product, you can provide information about the make and model, the products license plate number, the number of seats, and photos of the product. The processing of vehicle information is necessary for the performance of the contract with you (Article 6 (1) (b) of the GDPR) and KnockKnocks legitimate interest in providing the best possible services on the platform (article 6 (1) (f) of GDPR).',
    'When you interact with our service through various social media, such as when you connect through Facebook or when you like or post a comment on our Facebook page or interact with us on other social media, we may receive information from the social network, such as your profile information, profile photo, username, user ID associated with your social media account, age range, language, country, friends list, and any other information that you allow the social network to share with third parties. The data we receive depends on your privacy settings on the social network. The processing of this information is necessary for the performance of the contract with you (article 6 (1) (b) of the GDPR) and consent (article 6 (1) (a) of the GDPR). For more information, see our Facebook privacy policy.'=>'When you interact with our service through various social media, such as when you connect through Facebook or when you like or post a comment on our Facebook page or interact with us on other social media, we may receive information from the social network, such as your profile information, profile photo, username, user ID associated with your social media account, age range, language, country, friends list, and any other information that you allow the social network to share with third parties. The data we receive depends on your privacy settings on the social network. The processing of this information is necessary for the performance of the contract with you (article 6 (1) (b) of the GDPR) and consent (article 6 (1) (a) of the GDPR). For more information, see our Facebook privacy policy.',
    'We may also aggregate and anonymize your personal information and share that anonymous and/or aggregated information with third parties. This information is not personally identifiable and is used for industry and market analysis, demographic profiling, marketing and advertising, and other business purposes.'=>'We may also aggregate and anonymize your personal information and share that anonymous and/or aggregated information with third parties. This information is not personally identifiable and is used for industry and market analysis, demographic profiling, marketing and advertising, and other business purposes.',
    'We may review or analyze your communications (including messages sent to other users, comments included in trip or rental descriptions, and profile page content) on the platform for fraud prevention, risk assessment, compliance regulatory, research, product development, research and customer support. The processing of your personal data in this regard is based on our legitimate interest in the development of our products, research and customer support (article 6 (1) (f) of the GDPR and to comply with our legal obligations (article 6 (1) (c) of GDPR).'=>'We may review or analyze your communications (including messages sent to other users, comments included in trip or rental descriptions, and profile page content) on the platform for fraud prevention, risk assessment, compliance regulatory, research, product development, research and customer support. The processing of your personal data in this regard is based on our legitimate interest in the development of our products, research and customer support (article 6 (1) (f) of the GDPR and to comply with our legal obligations (article 6 (1) (c) of GDPR).',
    'We may share your name, email, phone number, and rental, ridesharing, or leasing activity on the Platform, in partnership with outside companies to provide you with additional KnockKnock-related services, for example, vouchers for soda at a gas station or a discount at a car wash.'=>'We may share your name, email, phone number, and rental, ridesharing, or leasing activity on the Platform, in partnership with outside companies to provide you with additional KnockKnock-related services, for example, vouchers for soda at a gas station or a discount at a car wash.',
    'You may request in writing copies of your personal information in our possession. We will provide you with a copy of the personal information in our possession as soon as possible, and in any event no later than 30 days after receiving a valid written request. We may request proof of identification to verify your identity and validate the request. If your personal information that we hold is inaccurate, please let us know and we will update the relevant information. You can also request the deletion of your personal data in accordance with the relevant data protection legislation. We will notify you within 30 days of your valid request of the relevant action taken.'=>'You may request in writing copies of your personal information in our possession. We will provide you with a copy of the personal information in our possession as soon as possible, and in any event no later than 30 days after receiving a valid written request. We may request proof of identification to verify your identity and validate the request. If your personal information that we hold is inaccurate, please let us know and we will update the relevant information. You can also request the deletion of your personal data in accordance with the relevant data protection legislation. We will notify you within 30 days of your valid request of the relevant action taken.',
    'KnockKnock may share your personal information, including name, address, mobile phone number, email, social security or national identity number, and information about your rental, rideshare, or leasing activity on KnockKnock. These service providers provide services on our behalf or otherwise assist in providing the service to you. KnockKnock may also request and receive from these service providers information about the status of your payment, pending payment or debt collection.'=>'KnockKnock may share your personal information, including name, address, mobile phone number, email, social security or national identity number, and information about your rental, rideshare, or leasing activity on KnockKnock. These service providers provide services on our behalf or otherwise assist in providing the service to you. KnockKnock may also request and receive from these service providers information about the status of your payment, pending payment or debt collection.',
    'We may also share personal information if necessary to comply with any applicable law or regulation or to enforce our Terms and Conditions, including the investigation of any violation or suspected criminal behavior.'=>'We may also share personal information if necessary to comply with any applicable law or regulation or to enforce our Terms and Conditions, including the investigation of any violation or suspected criminal behavior.',
